&lt;p&gt;On our first episode, we look at how collaboration happens in one of comedy's most storied (and tough) environments &mdash; the TV writers' room. It's where the magic happens, but it can also be one of the most brutally competitive places a creative person will ever work. We talk to two writer-comedians, Anne Lane and Wayne Federman, about their experiences working in writers' rooms on shows like &lt;em&gt;Rick and Morty&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Late Night with Jimmy Fallon&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
